33:56.234 --> 34:01.840 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
What you have got is a
circumstance that doesn't
comport with the stereotype of
what many people

34:01.940 --> 34:07.712 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
believe rape is like. It's a
white defendant,
someone who is -- comes from a
privileged

34:07.812 --> 34:12.050 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
background. Whatever his
financial status
before he attended Stanford, he
certainly

34:12.150 --> 34:22.527 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
comes from an elite institution,
was considered
an All-American swimmer, an
athlete of great

34:22.627 --> 34:29.668 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
import to the Stanford
community, and with
hopes of becoming an Olympic
athlete.

34:29.768 --> 34:35.507 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, those are the kinds of
factors, I think,
that color the way that the
media and the

34:35.607 --> 34:40.779 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
public have responded to this
case, someone
who comes from extraordinary
privilege, in

34:40.879 --> 34:49.554 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
a case that's fairly
straightforward, from
a -- from the -- given the fact
that there

34:49.654 --> 34:56.494 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
were witnesses and the evidence
in the form
of corroborative evidence on the
victim's

34:56.594 --> 34:58.396 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
body.

34:58.496 --> 35:02.233 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
These are unusual aspects of the
case. And
the disparity in privilege
between the defendant

35:02.334 --> 35:08.540 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
and the victim is also --
heightens the interest
in this kind of a case.

35:08.640 --> 35:14.112 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: I want to ask you
finally about
the letter the victim read to
the accused.

35:14.212 --> 35:19.651 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We haven't identified -- she
hasn't been identified,
but she read out loud in the
courtroom to

35:19.751 --> 35:23.755 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the accused man. She said -- and
this is part
of it -- she said: "I want to
show people

35:23.855 --> 35:30.328 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that one night of drinking can
ruin two lives,
you and me. You are the cause, I
am the effect.

35:30.428 --> 35:34.265 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You have dragged me through this
hell with
you, dipped me back into that
night again

35:34.366 --> 35:39.304 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and again. If you think I was
spared, came
out unscathed, that today I ride
off into

35:39.404 --> 35:43.808 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
