away their
dignity. But the notion that it
takes away

36:30.288 --> 36:35.093 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
one's possession of one's own
body and that
one wants to reject one's own
body, I found

36:35.193 --> 36:40.098 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that very powerful, and that
quotation has
come up and been reposted again
and again.

36:40.198 --> 36:44.569 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, it is
certainly -- this
is a case that has certainly
left, I think,

36:44.669 --> 36:46.805 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
an impact on many, many people.

36:46.905 --> 36:52.043 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Dean Michelle Anderson with the
City University
of New York Law School, thank
you very much.

36:52.143 --> 36:59.584 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MICHELLE ANDERSON: Thank you.

36:59.684 --> 37:08.026 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Public schools
are caught in
the middle of a political debate
over bathrooms.

37:08.126 --> 37:12.730 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Obama administration says
restricting
a transgender student's access
to restrooms

37:12.831 --> 37:18.603 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
and locker rooms based on
biological sex is
discrimination and can be
grounds for withholding

37:18.703 --> 37:20.438 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
funding.

37:20.538 --> 37:24.375 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But that directive has set off
some angry
reaction. Kentucky is one state
where many

37:24.476 --> 37:29.280 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
leaders don't agree with the
president. And
we look at how one school in
Louisville decided

37:29.380 --> 37:33.351 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to act proactively before the
bigger debate
began.

37:33.451 --> 37:38.089 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Special correspondent Yasmeen
Qureshi of Education
Week has the story. It's part of
our weekly

37:38.189 --> 37:40.992 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
education series, Making the
Grade.

37:41.092 --> 37:43.895 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
YASMEEN QURESHI: What's it like
to question
your gender?

37:43.995 --> 37:49.367 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MADDIE DALTON, Student, Atherton
High School:
It's a little bit scary in the
very beginning,

37:49.467 --> 37:53.938 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I suppose, because you know that
you're going
to have to face a lot of
discrimination.

37:54.038 --> 38:02.247 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Like, go through the YouTube
comments on any
video about trans people, and
you will see,

38:02.347 --> 38:07.685 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
like, just how many people are
still, like,
openly hostile to this idea.

38:07.785 --> 38:13.625 align:left position:25%,start line:73.33% size:75%
YASMEEN QURESHI:
Seventeen-year-old Maddie
Dalton is transgender. She says
she's always

38:13.725 --> 38:15.794 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
been a girl, but didn't know it.

38:15.894 --> 38:17.829 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
CASSANDRA KASEY, Parent:
Forever, she had
that little widow's peak.

38:17.929 --> 38:21.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
YASMEEN QURESHI: She came out to
her parents
when she was 15 years old.

38:21.766 --> 38:25.203 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
CASSANDRA KASEY: It was chaotic
at first.

38:25.303 --> 38:28.706 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And the way I felt it in the
very beginning,
when I was still coming to terms
with it,

38:28.806 --> 38:32.243 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
was, if I had a friend who came
to me and
said that their child had come
out to them

38:32.343 --> 38:36.814 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
as transgender, I would have
thought, hooray.
You know, your -- this young
person is becoming

38:36.915 --> 38:38.750 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
who they are.

38:38.850 --> 38:43.221 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, why would I not afford my
own child that
same -- that same blessing? So,
even though

38:43.321 --> 38:46.691 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
it was difficult, it was the
only right thing
to do.

38:46.791 --> 38:52.397 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
YASMEEN QURESHI: Maddie is a
junior at Atherton
High School in Louisville,
Kentucky. She was

38:52.497 --> 38:55.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the first openly transgender
student at the
school.

38:55.800 --> 39:02.707 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MADDIE DALTON: I was a little
bit hesitant
right at first, but I knew that,
being at

39:02.807 --> 39:06.144 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Atherton, I would be -- I would
be pretty
safe.

39:06.244 --> 39:11.149 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
YASMEEN QURESHI: A public high
school with
about 1,300 students, Atherton
is one of the

39:11.249 --> 39:16.354 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
highest-ranked schools in the
state. It's
known for its international
studies program

39:16.454 --> 39:19.524 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and as a place where diversity
is embraced.

39:19.624 --> 39:28.666 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TONY PRINCE, Teacher, Atherton
High School:
Developing a safe climate for
students is

39:28.766 --> 39:35.640 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
fundamental. And I think that we
did -- we
were doing that here before we
ever started

39:35.740 --> 39:37.609 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
on the transgender issue.

39:37.709 --> 39:43.281 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
YASMEEN QURESHI: Humanities
teacher Tony Prince
supervises the school's LGBT
student group.

39:43.381 --> 39:46.851 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Maddie confided in him about her
newly realized
gender identity.

39:46.951 --> 39:51.856 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TONY PRINCE: I asked her what
that means.
You know, what would the school
look like

39:51.956 --> 39:58.263 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to her if it were accepting of
her as a transgender
person? And so she wrote a
little list of

39:58.363 --> 40:00.064 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
things.

40:00.164 --> 40:06.404 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MADDIE DALTON: I wanted it to be
enforced
that students and teachers
should use my name

40:06.504 --> 40:13.111 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and pronouns and to use the
space that I identify
with, so bathrooms and locker
rooms.

40:13.211 --> 40:17.649 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
YASMEEN QURESHI: Atherton didn't
have a protocol
for transgender students. The
decision was

40:17.749 --> 40:19.617 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
left to principal Dr. Thomas
Aberli.

40:19.717 --> 40:23.921 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DR. THOMAS ABERLI, Principal,
Atherton High
School: Our school protects all
students,

40:24.022 --> 40:29.761 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and that the issue of gender
identity has
simply been a demonstration of
the school's

40:29.861 --> 40:33.031 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
commitment to respecting all
individuals in
our school.

40:33.131 --> 40:37.735 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
YASMEEN QURESHI: Aberli agreed
to Maddie's
requests and, after much
consideration, so

40:37.835 --> 40:43.441 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
did the school council, making
it the first
school in Kentucky to adopt an
official policy

40:43.541 --> 40:45.443 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
for transgender students.

40:45.543 --> 40:49.047 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAN: This policy is completely
disregarding
the privacy of all of their
students.

40:49.147 --> 40:53.818 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
YASMEEN QURESHI: A group of
parents, students
and community members publicly
objected and

40:53.918 --> 40:56.220 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
hired an attorney to appeal the
decision.

40:56.321 --> 41:01.125 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WOMAN: The girls at this school
expect to
be able to go into a restroom
and feel safe.

41:01.225 --> 41:03.461 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Because of this policy, we no
longer have
that assurance.

41:03.561 --> 41:08.833 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
YASMEEN QURESHI: The group
called for transgender
students to use a private or
unisex bathroom.

41:08.933 --> 41:10.702 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Why would that be a problem for
you?

41:10.802 --> 41:17.642 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MADDIE DALTON: First of all, it
makes you
a target for bullying and, like,
harassment.

41:17.742 --> 41:23.348 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It puts it in everyone's minds
that you are
different, and you are something
to be looked

41:23.448 --> 41:32.457 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
at, not as, like, a person, but
as whatever
characteristic is
differentiating you, like

41:32.557 --> 41:34.258 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
being trans.

41:34.359 --> 41:37.795 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
YASMEEN QURESHI: After months of
debate at
Atherton High School, the policy
was upheld,

41:37.895 --> 41:39.697 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
but the opposition didn't stop
there.

41:39.797 --> 41:43.368 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
KENT OSTRANDER, Executive
Director, The Family
Foundation: Young ladies, girls,
may not want

41:43.468 --> 41:49.507 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
