of The Family Foundation of
Kentucky, a conservative

41:56.481 --> 42:02.086 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
advocacy organization. Last
year, it supported
a statewide bill that would have
overturned

42:02.186 --> 42:05.456 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Atherton's policy. But it was
never passed
into law.

42:05.556 --> 42:11.662 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KENT OSTRANDER: The legislation
simply said
that schools could do all kinds
of accommodations

42:11.763 --> 42:16.000 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
for their students, including
transgender
students. But the one thing that
they could

42:16.100 --> 42:24.475 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
not do is put -- is mix the
biological sexes
in a bathroom, a locker room at
the same time.

42:24.575 --> 42:27.779 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
SUZANNE ECKES, Indiana
University: According
to guidelines coming from the
U.S. Department

42:27.879 --> 42:30.915 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
